Alongside these internal shifts, the week saw a deliberate reshaping of information and memory. Public health and climate data were among the first casualties. Following executive orders targeting DEI and \'93gender ideology,\'94 CDC webpages on contraception, STIs, HIV, and gender-affirming care disappeared or reappeared in stripped-down form. At NOAA, after a DOGE operative gained access to computer systems, some climate data vanished. HHS released a report documenting how private equity ownership of nursing homes increased patient deaths, but the news release announcing it was quietly removed from the agency\'92s website. These actions did not erase the underlying facts, but they made them harder for the public and researchers to find, and they signaled that evidence inconvenient to powerful interests could be buried. Memory was being curated by power.\
