Immigration enforcement agencies manipulated perception more directly. ICE updated timestamps on years-old press releases about raids and deportations, causing them to surface at the top of Google searches as if they were current. For immigrant communities already shaken by a surprise raid on farmworkers in Kern County, California, the effect was to amplify fear and confusion. When journalists at The Guardian reported on the practice, some of the updated dates disappeared from search results, suggesting a reactive effort to obscure the manipulation itself. At the same time, the FCC opened an investigation into a San Francisco radio station\'92s reporting on immigration raids and reinstated a news-distortion complaint tied to a Kamala Harris interview, while the White House canceled millions of dollars in POLITICO subscriptions based on a conspiracy theory about USAID funding. Trump publicly called for CBS and 60 Minutes to be \'93terminated\'94 over alleged editing of that interview. Together, these moves used regulatory and economic levers, as well as presidential rhetoric, to pressure media outlets that challenged the administration\'92s narratives. Independent media were starved while state-aligned voices thrived.\
